Senator representing Plateau South at the National Assembly, Prof Nora Ladi Daduut has felicitated with Muslims as they mark the end of this year’s Ramadan fasting. This was contained in a statement made available to newsmen in Jos on Sunday. “For the past thirty (30) days, Muslims the world over have observed the fasting in the sacred month of Ramadan in compliance with the Islamic injunction. She called on all Muslims to be steadfast in applying the virtues of Ramadan. Senator Daduut urged Nigerians to remain steadfast and committed to the cause of one united and developed country She called on all Nigerians to live in harmony with one another irrespective of ethnic or religious affiliation. The Senator vowed to continue to put the interest of the citizens of Plateau South first at all times.